1
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:06,000
(Male tout) Brother, today...

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:14,000
♬〜

3
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:17,000
(Suguro Hanji) Hey, don't you know this girl?

4
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:19,000
(Male tout) No... I don't understand.

5
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:25,000
(Suguro) Hey, don't you know this kid?

6
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:27,000
I don't know.

7
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:37,000
♬〜

8
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:39,000
(impact sound)

9
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:43,000
(Tsubomi Kizawa) Itter!

10
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:45,000
(Salesperson) Huh?

11
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:47,000
No, I can't believe it's this expensive...

12
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:49,000
My wallet hurts so much.

13
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:52,000
The bonus is gone!

14
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:55,000
(Clerk) Congratulations on your engagement.

15
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:59,000
But... there's still nothing like a proposal...

16
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:01,000
We're not even dating.

17
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:05,000
Huh? What you purchased was an engagement ring, right?

18
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:07,000
That's right!

19
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:11,000
I want to date someone with the intention of getting married.

20
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:15,000
I just said... I thought I would give it to you as a surprise!

21
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:17,000
(Mobile phone ringtone)

22
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:19,000
(Cellphone ringtone) Excuse me.

23
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:23,000
Yes, it's a bud.

24
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:25,000
Move out!?

25
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:29,000
<This story is about seven unique detectives.>

26
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:35,000
This is a drama about a moving investigation headquarters vehicle, commonly known as Ichibanboshi, that solves cases.

27
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:48,000
(Norifumi Akase) Buds!

28
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:50,000
This is the scene.

29
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:59,000
♬〜

30
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:01,000
Please see above.

31
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:05,000
(Investigator) Which station? Don't touch the scene without permission!

32
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:08,000
(Investigator) This is our scene! (Investigator) Just go home!

33
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:12,000
(Investigator) Noisy! It's under my jurisdiction. Back off now!

34
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:15,000
What do you mean?

35
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:19,000
A man collapsed in front of an apartment around 5 o'clock this morning →

36
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:21,000
discovered by a resident.

37
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:25,000
The apartment complex has building A and building B →

38
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:29,000
As a man's footprints were discovered on the roof of Building A→

39
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:31,000
It is believed that it fell from Building A.

40
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:33,000
Here's where it gets tricky.

41
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:35,000
(Momoko Nakazawa) What?

42
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:42,000
This apartment is located on the border between Shinjuku and Nakano wards.

43
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:45,000
So, the addresses of Building A and Building B are different.

44
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:49,000
yes. This Building A is Kitagicho, Shinjuku Ward.

45
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:52,000
This Building B is in Nakagamicho, Nakano Ward.

46
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:56,000
The jurisdictional police station in charge of each is different.

47
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:59,000
It must have fallen from Building A over here.

48
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:02,000
Isn't that the jurisdiction of Shinjuku Ward?

49
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:06,000
This is the exact location of the body where it fell.

50
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:08,000
On the site on the Nakano Ward side of Building B.

51
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:14,000
That means it fell from the roof of Building A onto the grounds of Building B.

52
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:16,000
That's right... I see...

53
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:18,000
(Suguro) Wait a minute!

54
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:20,000
something? something?

55
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:22,000
Why are you guys going ahead alone?

56
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:25,000
It's probably an investigative meeting held by everyone.

57
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:28,000
(Hiroshi Shiratori) They don't notice us.

58
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:32,000
(Mio Amao) Hmm. There is a limit to how close we are.

59
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:34,000
(Everyone laughs) No...

60
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:37,000
And any other information?

61
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:39,000
Same as always.

62
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:42,000
Neither Kabukicho Police Station nor Higashi-Nakano Police Station will tell me anything.

63
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:44,000
What!? First...

64
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:46,000
what?

65
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:49,000
Oh no... Go ahead.

66
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:52,000
Something I'm curious about.

67
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:54,000
lend me.

68
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:56,000
If I committed suicide →

69
00:03:56,000 --> 00:04:00,000
Fall from the rooftop along the wall.

70
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:05,000
However, the body was located on the side of Building B, more than 10 meters away from the wall of Building A.

71
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:09,000
There's a possibility that he was thrown, which means he was murdered.

72
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:11,000
Maybe so.

73
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:15,000
I'm sorry. Will it cause trouble?

74
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:19,000
If it was a murder, any police station would set up an investigation headquarters.

75
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:22,000
Honestly, every police station likes to set up an investigation headquarters.

76
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:25,000
Yeah. When it comes to murder, the police station becomes excited and becomes one.

77
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:27,000
The budget will also go down.

78
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Okay. Everyone please collect information.

79
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:32,000
(All) Yes.

80
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:50,000
ᗕ(sound of door opening)

81
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:53,000
We were flirting. I haven't.

82
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:03,000
Mobile Investigation Division. Please show me the scene.

83
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:05,000
Thank you for your hard work. ᗕ(Naohiro Kazano) Hey Nakazawa!

84
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:09,000
Which side did you put down?

85
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:11,000
Huh?

86
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:13,000
(Voice of Kazano) After the commotion caused by illegal arrest→

87
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:17,000
We were criticized so much that our budget was cut.

88
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:19,000
You smeared mud on my face!

89
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:25,000
Momoko: Were you at Higashi-Nakano police station?

90
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:27,000
My previous boss.

91
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:31,000
I'll leave the rest to you, Mio-nee.

92
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:34,000
Got it. See you then.

93
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,000
Shit.

94
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:42,000
Senpai! Did you find anything left behind?

95
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:44,000
no….

96
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:46,000
I see.

97
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:49,000
Yeah….

98
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:55,000
(Mio) I see.

99
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:57,000
It fell from there.

100
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:02,000
Thank you for your hard work.

101
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:08,000
Hey, me, me. I'm a hard worker.

102
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:10,000
yes.

103
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:12,000
Did you have your smartphone or wallet left?

104
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:14,000
home.

105
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:16,000
Ah, that's right.

106
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:22,000
Hey, me. What is that?

107
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:25,000
(Investigator) Now... what do you want.

108
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:42,000
please.

109
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:51,000
Now, let's begin the investigation meeting.

110
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:55,000
Please report any information you have gathered so far.

111
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:04,000
All we know is that the person who died was a young man.

112
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:06,000
Even small details are fine.

113
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:08,000
We don't know anything yet.

114
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:10,000
What about Higashi Nakano Police Station?

115
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:12,000
There is nothing to report either.

116
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:15,000
Don't hide it.

117
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:17,000
The results of the autopsy are out.

118
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:19,000
(clicks tongue)

119
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:25,000
(Bio) The corpse's skull was cracked from the back of the head to the side of the head.

120
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:28,000
There was a contusion wound caused by being hit with something like a blunt object →

121
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:31,000
Death due to brain contusion.

122
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:34,000
Then it's murder.

123
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:37,000
(Mio) It seems almost certain.

124
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:43,000
Could you please talk to each other and set up a joint investigation headquarters at one of the police stations?

125
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:46,000
The site straddles two wards →

126
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:48,000
There is one incident.

127
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:51,000
What do you think?

128
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:54,000
What do you think?

129
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:02,000
It can't be helped.

130
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:07,000
We, the Mobile Investigation Division, received a direct order from the Deputy Director-General of the National Police Agency →

131
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:10,000
Direct joint investigation.

132
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:15,000
From now on, this is the investigation headquarters!

133
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:17,000
Wait. what do you want?

134
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:20,000
Nakazawa: Let me do it.

135
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:22,000
Please tell Kabukicho Police Station to pull me over.

136
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:25,000
(Kabukicho Police Station Investigator) Is that how it works? The crime scene is on this side. Draw that one!

137
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:27,000
Nakazawa!

138
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:31,000
If you're not repentant, atone for it!

139
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:35,000
(Sound of tapping on desk) I am the head of the Joint Investigation Headquarters!

140
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:40,000
This murder case will be jointly investigated by both police departments.

141
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:45,000
Let's throw away our territoriality and join forces!

142
00:08:45,000 --> 00:09:07,000
♬〜

143
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:10,000
Is it a leftover item?

144
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:13,000
Yeah~…!?

145
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:16,000
Ah... no...

146
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:19,000
(Teruhiko Nemoto) It's as big as ever and it's a nuisance. Ichibanboshi!

147
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:24,000
♬〜

148
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:26,000
Ah...!

149
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:28,000
What are you doing?

150
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:30,000
The things I bought are gone.

151
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:34,000
What is it?

152
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:39,000
Are you excited because it's your first kill in a while?

153
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:44,000
But but! This time, Ichibanboshi's performance is not seen.

154
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:47,000
Huh? (Nemoto) You are no longer needed.

155
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:50,000
(Yu Masuda) Higashi-Nakano Police Station and Kabukicho Police Station met →

156
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:53,000
We decided to set up a joint investigation headquarters at Kabukicho Police Station.

157
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:56,000
Huh? Seriously?

158
00:09:56,000 --> 00:10:00,000
I see... That's right….

159
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:02,000
Why are you disappointed?

160
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:04,000
The idea is to set up a joint investigation headquarters and have them carry out the investigation in a friendly manner.

161
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:06,000
It's your earnest wish.

162
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:08,000
Yeah. Well, well... well.

163
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:12,000
It was. Then I have to be happy.

164
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:17,000
Yay! I can go home! You can watch anime! I can take a nap!

165
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:19,000
It seems contrived!

166
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:25,000
♬〜

167
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:27,000
Detectives from Higashi-Nakano Police Station...

168
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:30,000
So, I guess we've settled on a joint agreement after all.

169
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:33,000
ᗒChief!

170
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:37,000
Why did you join the Joint Investigation Headquarters?

171
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:41,000
That's what the manager over there said. Throw away your sense of territory.

172
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:44,000
I think that's certainly true.

173
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:47,000
Same police. We need to help each other.

174
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:51,000
We'll do the rest.

175
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:54,000
(sigh)

176
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:57,000
That's a lie. Absolutely a lie!

177
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:59,000
As expected, I could hear the noise too.

178
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:01,000
What should we do?

179
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:03,000
Momoko's face is cracked, so search around her.

180
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:07,000
I sneak into the investigation meeting. Then→

181
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:09,000
Use honorific language for older people.

182
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:12,000
Kuro-san...

183
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:19,000
Oh? Oh?

184
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:23,000
there were!

185
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:28,000
Oh no...

186
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:30,000
Something inside is missing!

187
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:32,000
what happened?

188
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:35,000
Oh no... it's nothing.

189
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:40,000
It's a surprise present.

190
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:50,000
(cell phone vibration sound)

191
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:53,000
(cell phone vibrating sound) Ah.

192
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:55,000
yes. Mr. Kuro.

193
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:58,000
(Suguro) I infiltrated the investigation meeting, but it seems strange.

194
00:11:58,000 --> 00:12:01,000
Higashi-Nakano Police Station and Kabukicho Police Station...

195
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:04,000
Huh? what?

196
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:07,000
It seems like they have a secret pact.

197
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:09,000
A secret deal? (Notification sound)

198
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:13,000
Ah, Chief, there's a new investigation command order. Huh?

199
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:15,000
Ah, Kuro-san, I'll use the speaker.

200
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:21,000
The mobile investigation headquarters vehicle maintains its location.

201
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:24,000
Continue to lead the joint investigation.

202
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:26,000
What do you mean?

203
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:30,000
A joint investigation headquarters was set up, right? Then we don't need it...?

204
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:37,000
♬〜

205
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:39,000
ᗒKuro-san!

206
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:46,000
What do you mean? It's a secret agreement.

207
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:51,000
I'm talking about a man named Naru Sasaki...

208
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:56,000
Detectives name it.

209
00:12:56,000 --> 00:13:00,000
Everyone knew about it and was secretly talking about it behind my back.

210
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:02,000
He said he killed her.

211
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:04,000
Did you kill it?

212
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:10,000
He was warned for his problematic behavior. He committed a violent act at a sex shop in Shinjuku.

213
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:13,000
I'm currently off work. I can't contact you.

214
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:15,000
Who is Satoshi Sasaki?

215
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:23,000
A police officer at Kabukicho Police Station.

216
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:31,000
(Suguro) Are you coming to play? His name is Sasaki Osamu.

217
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:36,000
(Salesperson) I don't know. I don't remember each customer's face.

218
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:41,000
(Suguro) You guys have nice noses, don't you? And the police officer is a high-ranking customer.

219
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:43,000
Because I'm stressed out!!

220
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:48,000
(Manager) We are open for business. Hahaha. Please give me a break.

221
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:52,000
Hey, are you going to hide it? Like my daughter!

222
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:56,000
That's why my daughter doesn't work at our house.

223
00:13:56,000 --> 00:14:00,000
I don't even know where you are! What are you?

224
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:03,000
Say it...!! You bastard!! No, no!

225
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:09,000
Everyone at the investigation headquarters suspects me, but they don't mention my name at the meeting.

226
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:13,000
Apparently there was pressure from above.

227
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:15,000
Hide your family's crime.

228
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:19,000
The local authorities feel the same way.

229
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:23,000
I don't want to catch my friends and it will be a big problem.

230
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:28,000
Are you trying to gloss over the incident without naming the suspects?

231
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:33,000
Is that a secret agreement?

232
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:38,000
Yeah. A secret agreement not to put his name on the investigation trail.

233
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:45,000
Move to Kabukicho Police Station.

234
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:55,000
(Suguro) I told you about my daughter Miku before.

235
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:59,000
I got addicted to hosting and racked up debt.

236
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:02,000
Then he went missing.

237
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:06,000
Apparently she's working in the sex industry to pay off her debts...

238
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:09,000
Hey, what is debt? I heard it from my mother.

239
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:14,000
(Suguro's voice) I was so busy with work that I didn't know anything about my daughter.

240
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:19,000
Actually, I don't have any right to be angry. Because it was originally my fault.

241
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:27,000
When I found my daughter →

242
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:29,000
It's the day I quit being a detective.

243
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:37,000
Sorry for the boring story.

244
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:39,000
Oh no...

245
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:42,000
Would you like to talk about something bright?

246
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:46,000
Momoko consulted me this morning.

247
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:52,000
Did you ask me to go out with you?

248
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:58,000
yes. assuming marriage.

249
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:05,000
(Mio) Hehe, are you serious? Are you dating with the intention of getting married?

250
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:09,000
Well, I was kind of happy, though.

251
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:15,000
Momoko. Huh?

252
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:17,000
Still can't forget?

253
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:29,000
(Momoko's voice) A stranger stabbed me in the back with a knife...

254
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:31,000
He's not breathing anymore...

255
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:43,000
♬〜

256
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:47,000
I'm planning to propose after this incident is over.

257
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:50,000
Ah... ah...!

258
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:52,000
Haha...!

259
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:58,000
So... what's the reason for that gloomy face?

260
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:04,000
Kuro-san... please listen to me.

261
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:08,000
Where's my engagement ring?

262
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:13,000
Arrived at Kabukicho Police Station.

263
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:19,000
(Police Officer) Ichibanboshi! The first star has arrived!

264
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:24,000
(Police Officer) Chief! The first star...!

265
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:26,000
Huh? Ah...!

266
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:30,000
Ah, beautiful sister. Yeah?

267
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:35,000
(Swan) This was found at the scene. It may be related to the incident.

268
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:37,000
Yeah? what? this.

269
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:41,000
Did it belong to the victim or did the suspect drop it?

270
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:44,000
Hmm….

271
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:47,000
(Mio) Huh? Ah... (Swan) Huh? What happened?

272
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:50,000
I couldn't take it anymore... (Swan) Why are you letting it in?

273
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:52,000
What should I do...

274
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:56,000
Why are you here? Joint Investigation Headquarters stand up!

275
00:17:56,000 --> 00:18:01,000
Well, some information came to me that I couldn't let go of.

276
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:03,000
Did you understand something? Nemo-chan.

277
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:05,000
"Mr. Nemoto." You have a strange sense of distance.

278
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:07,000
The identity of the victim has been determined.

279
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:09,000
Kazuhiko Maruyama.

280
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:11,000
I lived in that apartment.

281
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:15,000
I'm scouting for sex shops in Shinjuku. 23 years old.

282
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:18,000
23 years old!? A sex shop in Shinjuku?

283
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:20,000
What is it?

284
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:24,000
The important reference person we found also caused trouble at a sex shop in Shinjuku.

285
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:28,000
A 23-year-old police officer.

286
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:31,000
Police officer!? Really!?

287
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:33,000
I'll pretend I didn't ask.

288
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:36,000
Stop sticking your neck out because it's such a hassle.

289
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:40,000
Okay? Don't seriously think about the meaning of justice.

290
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:44,000
Ah... I'm already looking. Kuro-san and Bud.

291
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:46,000
You guys work too fast!

292
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:49,000
Ah, don't praise this.

293
00:18:49,000 --> 00:19:14,000
♬〜

294
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:18,000
(Knock) (Shingo Akase) Please.

295
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:26,000
♬〜

296
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:29,000
I came here to confirm.

297
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:33,000
Why was a joint investigation headquarters set up, but we were in command?

298
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:38,000
(Shingo) As we proceeded with the investigation, we found out, right?

299
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:45,000
Ah...it looks like there was a crime committed by a police officer.

300
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:47,000
What is your policy there?

301
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:51,000
Justice is not something that can be brandished everywhere.

302
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:54,000
Doesn't that make you look like an idiot?

303
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:57,000
Justice also has TPO.

304
00:19:57,000 --> 00:20:00,000
I heard it for the first time.

305
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:03,000
In a world where people aren't stupid, it's a common phrase.

306
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:05,000
You'd better remember it soon.

307
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:18,000
When the incident comes to light, it is criticized and investigated by the public.

308
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:20,000
Shame on the police.

309
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:26,000
Brother... what should I do?

310
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:29,000
Clean.

311
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:34,000
This is my first job.

312
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:40,000
Show that the power of the police is absolute and has no signs of fraying.

313
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:47,000
Cooperate with the local authorities to cover up the incident.

314
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:53,000
You take command.

315
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:58,000
If everything goes well, I'll let it out of the cage.

316
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:32,000
♬〜

317
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:35,000
Mr. Kuro.

318
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:41,000
Suspect Police Officer Please find and secure him.

319
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:49,000
♬〜

320
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:56,000
♬〜

321
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:58,000
(Salesperson) Hey! Don't come in...

322
00:21:58,000 --> 00:22:00,000
It's the police.

323
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:04,000
(Suguro) Hey, here it is! Manager of an illegal store!

324
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:06,000
I'm looking for a man named Naru Sasaki.

325
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:09,000
If you don't know his name, it's the guy who always stands at the police box in Kabukicho.

326
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:11,000
You were a customer, right?

327
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:15,000
He's involved in a murder case.

328
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:20,000
I asked you! Look here!

329
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:22,000
I refuse because it's optional.

330
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:27,000
I reported him to the police website because he touched my subordinate.

331
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:30,000
Hahahaha…! This bastard...!

332
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:34,000
It's the police. Please come out once.

333
00:22:34,000 --> 00:22:36,000
(Salesperson) Hey! Don't do anything selfish! (Suguro) Cola!

334
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:40,000
It's the police! Please come out. I have something I want to ask you, so please come out.

335
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:44,000
It's the police! It's the police!

336
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:50,000
♬〜

337
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:54,000
I'm going to arrest them all on suspicion of violating the Entertainment Business Act!

338
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:58,000
If you don't like it, turn to me and answer!

339
00:22:58,000 --> 00:23:08,000
♬〜

340
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:10,000
Mr. Kuro?

341
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:19,000
♬〜

342
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:21,000
No way...

343
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:31,000
♬〜

344
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:33,000
Dad is worried about you.

345
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:36,000
I was looking for you.

346
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:43,000
(sigh)

347
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:46,000
A police officer reported that he had been beaten.

348
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:48,000
I didn't hit him or anything.

349
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:52,000
You got hit, right? Yeah.

350
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:54,000
You guys, don't lie!

351
00:23:57,000 --> 00:24:02,000
(Miku Suguro) I saw it. That person gets hit.

352
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:04,000
To that old man.

353
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:13,000
Please stop looking for Officer Sasaki.

354
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:19,000
Get out of this town!

355
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:21,000
But...

356
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:30,000
♬〜

357
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:32,000
Mr. Kuro!

358
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:38,000
♬〜

359
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:41,000
Mr. Kuro! Mr. Kuro!

360
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:43,000
We are in the middle of an investigation!

361
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:48,000
That's about my daughter...

362
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:50,000
We have to find the suspect!

363
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:56,000
It's my fault. Miku started hanging out at the host club...

364
00:24:58,000 --> 00:25:04,000
When he was at the local police station, he arrested a student from the same high school as Miku in pursuit of a violent incident.

365
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:08,000
As a result, Miku stopped going to school.

366
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:13,000
``Why didn't you let me miss you, since you're my classmate?'' I was asked.

367
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:15,000
All I could say was, "Because it's work."

368
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:22,000
What!? It’s okay! Please come!

369
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:24,000
Hey…!

370
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:29,000
(Salesperson) Is there something wrong with you yet?

371
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:32,000
(Kazeno) Please do whatever you want! Don't make any more noise!

372
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:34,000
Please let me say one thing!

373
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:36,000
Mr. Miku.

374
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:45,000
My father was also there.

375
00:25:45,000 --> 00:25:50,000
I worked as a long-distance truck driver and was devoted to my job.

376
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:59,000
When I was naughty too, a detective noticed me.

377
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:05,000
But that saved me.

378
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:13,000
The detective scolded me on behalf of my father, who was away at work.

379
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:18,000
I'm still grateful.

380
00:26:18,000 --> 00:26:20,000
that's why….

381
00:26:20,000 --> 00:26:28,000
♬〜

382
00:26:28,000 --> 00:26:31,000
Dad did nothing wrong!

383
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:35,000
I did my job to protect the safety of the public!

384
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:37,000
(Miku) I was bullied!

385
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:39,000
My friends call me a traitor.

386
00:26:42,000 --> 00:26:45,000
I was also poor and bullied. (Miku) Then you'll understand!

387
00:26:45,000 --> 00:26:47,000
I get bullied for being weak.

388
00:26:47,000 --> 00:26:50,000
What's wrong with being weak?

389
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:53,000
Shouldn't the weak be allowed to live?

390
00:26:57,000 --> 00:26:59,000
Dad said.

391
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:06,000
When I found you →

392
00:27:06,000 --> 00:27:09,000
Even when I quit being a detective.

393
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:15,000
(Suguro) Buds….

394
00:27:19,000 --> 00:27:21,000
Enough is enough.

395
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:35,000
♬〜

396
00:27:35,000 --> 00:27:39,000
Sorry for going too far...

397
00:27:40,000 --> 00:27:44,000
You're an idiot, but you're a good guy.

398
00:27:46,000 --> 00:27:48,000
ᗕ(Miku) Dad!

399
00:27:55,000 --> 00:28:00,000
I know... someone called Sasaki.

400
00:28:00,000 --> 00:28:02,000
Huh...?

401
00:28:02,000 --> 00:28:06,000
I came to the store many times and got into a fight with the scout guy.

402
00:28:06,000 --> 00:28:11,000
I was trying to take out a girl from the shop named Mari.

403
00:28:12,000 --> 00:28:14,000
The apartment where Mari lives.

404
00:28:20,000 --> 00:28:25,000
♬〜

405
00:28:25,000 --> 00:28:29,000
Hey, do you want to go home with your dad?

406
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:35,000
Impossible. I still have debt. It's still increasing.

407
00:28:39,000 --> 00:28:41,000
Please tell Kuro-san too!

408
00:28:41,000 --> 00:28:46,000
(Suguro) Miku: What can your father do?

409
00:28:48,000 --> 00:28:52,000
I'll quit my job if you'll come back.

410
00:28:56,000 --> 00:29:01,000
Don't worry anymore. Because I'm never going home.

411
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:10,000
Then please stay alive.

412
00:29:10,000 --> 00:29:12,000
Promise me that much.

413
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:14,000
Kuro-san, let's take him home!

414
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:16,000
It's okay.

415
00:29:17,000 --> 00:29:20,000
If only you were alive...

416
00:29:23,000 --> 00:29:26,000
Live!

417
00:29:26,000 --> 00:29:28,000
that's why….

418
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:34,000
Dad also continues to be a detective.

419
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:52,000
♬〜

420
00:29:54,000 --> 00:30:01,000
♬〜

421
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:03,000
(chime)

422
00:30:07,000 --> 00:30:12,000
I'm a police officer. Mari Hagiwara, right?

423
00:30:14,000 --> 00:30:16,000
ᗒ (noise)

424
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:18,000
Bud: There's someone inside... yes!

425
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:27,000
♬〜

426
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:36,000
My name is Osamu Sasaki from the Kabukicho Police Station Regional Division.

427
00:30:36,000 --> 00:30:42,000
♬〜

428
00:30:42,000 --> 00:30:44,000
Understood.

429
00:30:45,000 --> 00:30:48,000
chef. Please issue number 2.

430
00:30:53,934 --> 00:30:55,934
(tire squealing sound)

431
00:30:55,934 --> 00:31:08,934
♬〜

432
00:31:08,934 --> 00:31:10,934
What is this car?

433
00:31:12,934 --> 00:31:15,934
It's a hindrance... Go home!

434
00:31:15,934 --> 00:31:17,934
ᗒWhat is it this time?

435
00:31:17,934 --> 00:31:23,934
♬〜

436
00:31:23,934 --> 00:31:28,934
Could you hand me Officer Sasaki? We'll handle the interrogation.

437
00:31:28,934 --> 00:31:40,934
♬〜

438
00:31:45,934 --> 00:31:49,934
(Funo) Is it fun? Catch a relative.

439
00:31:49,934 --> 00:31:52,934
Do you want credit that much?

440
00:31:52,934 --> 00:31:58,934
A person who doesn't consider his friends to be his friends is not a police officer!

441
00:32:00,934 --> 00:32:02,934
(Suguro) Let's go.

442
00:32:05,934 --> 00:32:07,934
(sigh)

443
00:32:09,934 --> 00:32:12,934
I don't really understand justice or anything like that...

444
00:32:15,934 --> 00:32:17,934
I don't like crooked things.

445
00:32:32,934 --> 00:32:36,934
(Suguro) What the hell happened? To you and the victim.

446
00:32:37,934 --> 00:32:42,934
I caused trouble for the people at the police station...

447
00:32:42,934 --> 00:32:48,934
That's a story for later. We want to know the reality of the matter.

448
00:32:52,934 --> 00:32:55,934
(Mari Hagiwara) That person is a regular customer of mine and we became friends...

449
00:32:55,934 --> 00:32:58,934
I don't know anything else.

450
00:33:03,934 --> 00:33:08,934
(Mio) You know what this is, right? It is used in a competition called Molukku.

451
00:33:08,934 --> 00:33:12,934
...I don't know anything about that at all.

452
00:33:13,934 --> 00:33:16,934
Did you have a good time? When I was in high school.

453
00:33:24,934 --> 00:33:29,934
You three are high school classmates, right?

454
00:33:32,934 --> 00:33:35,934
After graduating...→

455
00:33:35,934 --> 00:33:37,934
One is a police officer →

456
00:33:37,934 --> 00:33:40,934
One person is an entertainment scout→

457
00:33:40,934 --> 00:33:42,934
The girl becomes a prostitute.

458
00:33:42,934 --> 00:33:44,934
No!

459
00:33:45,934 --> 00:33:50,934
Mari was sunk by that guy.

460
00:33:53,934 --> 00:33:58,934
(voice) It was around the time when we couldn't even hold a graduation ceremony due to the coronavirus.

461
00:33:58,934 --> 00:34:02,934
Kazuhiko invited me to play Molukku...

462
00:34:02,934 --> 00:34:06,934
We were good friends.

463
00:34:06,934 --> 00:34:09,934
Until I graduate...

464
00:34:09,934 --> 00:34:14,934
♬〜

465
00:34:14,934 --> 00:34:16,934
ᗒ(Kazuhiko Maruyama) Good evening.

466
00:34:16,934 --> 00:34:19,934
(voice) I graduated from high school and became a police officer→

467
00:34:19,934 --> 00:34:26,934
Kazuhiko dropped out of university and worked as an entertainment scout.

468
00:34:26,934 --> 00:34:29,934
(Kazuhiko) Ichi!? What are you doing?

469
00:34:29,934 --> 00:34:31,934
(Kazuhiko) What is that dress?

470
00:34:31,934 --> 00:34:33,934
No, I became a police officer.

471
00:34:37,934 --> 00:34:39,934
(voice) Around the same time...

472
00:34:39,934 --> 00:34:41,934
(Excuse) Hey, thank you.

473
00:34:41,934 --> 00:34:45,934
(voice) I got a call from Mari...

474
00:34:45,934 --> 00:34:48,934
I want you to help me...

475
00:34:48,934 --> 00:34:55,934
When I was attending university, I got a call from Kazuhiko and was invited to join the host club...

476
00:34:55,934 --> 00:35:01,934
So I got addicted to hosting and got into debt →

477
00:35:01,934 --> 00:35:06,934
I'm working at a delivery health service to pay the bills...

478
00:35:06,934 --> 00:35:09,934
I understand because I'm a police officer.

479
00:35:11,934 --> 00:35:16,934
Why Mari got addicted to hosting and why she went into debt →

480
00:35:16,934 --> 00:35:18,934
Kazuhiko arranged it.

481
00:35:20,934 --> 00:35:22,934
(Soundbite) He's got money, too.

482
00:35:25,934 --> 00:35:30,934
(Apologetic voice) She tried to talk to her parents and the police →

483
00:35:30,934 --> 00:35:32,934
I controlled it by force.

484
00:35:32,934 --> 00:35:44,934
♬〜

485
00:35:44,934 --> 00:35:46,934
Please take my place...

486
00:35:46,934 --> 00:36:00,934
♬〜

487
00:36:00,934 --> 00:36:04,934
(Mari) I came to the delivery health office many times.

488
00:36:05,934 --> 00:36:09,934
Let's quit this job and go home.

489
00:36:09,934 --> 00:36:15,934
But Kazuhiko brushed me off because I agreed with him...

490
00:36:17,934 --> 00:36:21,934
It's okay because I work here. What about (paraphrase)?

491
00:36:21,934 --> 00:36:24,934
(Mio's voice) You wanted to get out of there, right?

492
00:36:24,934 --> 00:36:27,934
(Mari's voice) Because Kazuhiko is violent →

493
00:36:27,934 --> 00:36:30,934
All I can say is that I'm doing it because I want to do it...

494
00:36:33,934 --> 00:36:38,934
I... I trampled on Yuno's feelings.

495
00:36:39,934 --> 00:36:43,934
I wanted to save Mari somehow.

496
00:36:45,934 --> 00:36:49,934
(voice) I invited Kazuhiko to play Morukku.

497
00:36:51,934 --> 00:36:57,934
(sigh) I wanted to make sure that we still had a friendship like we used to.

498
00:36:58,934 --> 00:37:01,934
(Kazuhiko) That's nonsense, police officer.

499
00:37:01,934 --> 00:37:05,934
It's not boring. Let's do it, Kazuhiko.

500
00:37:05,934 --> 00:37:08,934
Let's remember when we were in high school. What?

501
00:37:08,934 --> 00:37:10,934
Everyone was friendly.

502
00:37:10,934 --> 00:37:13,934
Haha... when was that?

503
00:37:13,934 --> 00:37:15,934
Time is up, idiot.

504
00:37:17,934 --> 00:37:20,934
(Kazuhiko) There's a bratty police officer!

505
00:37:21,934 --> 00:37:34,934
♬〜

506
00:37:34,934 --> 00:37:36,934
(sound of hitting)

507
00:37:36,934 --> 00:37:54,934
♬〜

508
00:37:54,934 --> 00:37:56,934
In memory of the three of us...

509
00:37:56,934 --> 00:38:04,934
♬〜

510
00:38:04,934 --> 00:38:06,934
I felt like I was being spat on...

511
00:38:06,934 --> 00:38:12,934
♬〜

512
00:38:12,934 --> 00:38:17,934
If only my daughter had a friend like you...

513
00:38:18,934 --> 00:38:20,934
You're wrong.

514
00:38:25,934 --> 00:38:29,934
I have no sympathy for the fact that you killed someone.

515
00:38:29,934 --> 00:38:31,934
It's your fault.

516
00:38:31,934 --> 00:38:33,934
Me?

517
00:38:35,934 --> 00:38:38,934
I'll say it clearly. you are wrong

518
00:38:38,934 --> 00:38:40,934
What is it!?

519
00:38:40,934 --> 00:38:43,934
Because I'm clinging to memories!

520
00:38:43,934 --> 00:38:47,934
When you grow up, you can become depressed and sad.

521
00:38:47,934 --> 00:38:49,934
But at times like that→

522
00:38:49,934 --> 00:38:54,934
This is what happens when you look back on the past instead of facing the present.

523
00:38:57,934 --> 00:39:00,934
There's no point in looking back.

524
00:39:00,934 --> 00:39:02,934
Nothing progresses.

525
00:39:04,934 --> 00:39:06,934
I have to look ahead and live.

526
00:39:11,934 --> 00:39:13,934
I'm still alive!

527
00:39:13,934 --> 00:39:26,934
♬〜

528
00:39:26,934 --> 00:39:29,934
Osamu Sasaki admitted to the crime.

529
00:39:33,934 --> 00:39:35,934
I will send the person to the Metropolitan Police Department.

530
00:39:38,934 --> 00:39:40,934
(Swan) This is it.

531
00:39:40,934 --> 00:39:46,934
♬〜

532
00:39:46,934 --> 00:39:48,934
(Ichita Hagiwara) Mari….

533
00:39:48,934 --> 00:39:50,934
(Mari) Papa!

534
00:39:52,934 --> 00:39:54,934
(sob)

535
00:39:56,934 --> 00:39:59,934
it was good. If we can never meet again...

536
00:40:01,934 --> 00:40:03,934
sorry….

537
00:40:03,934 --> 00:40:05,934
Dad...

538
00:40:05,934 --> 00:40:07,934
Dad, I'm sorry...

539
00:40:07,934 --> 00:40:09,934
(Mari's crying)

540
00:40:09,934 --> 00:40:11,934
(Mari) Dad...

541
00:40:11,934 --> 00:40:15,934
(Mari's crying)

542
00:40:26,934 --> 00:40:28,934
What are you doing?

543
00:40:29,934 --> 00:40:31,934
No, not really...

544
00:40:31,934 --> 00:40:34,934
I've been looking for you all day today.

545
00:40:34,934 --> 00:40:37,934
Um... no, it's really nothing.

546
00:40:37,934 --> 00:40:39,934
bud….

547
00:40:42,934 --> 00:40:44,934
yes.

548
00:40:45,934 --> 00:40:48,934
I don't have the guts to remain silent, so I'm going to vomit!

549
00:40:50,934 --> 00:40:52,934
actually….

550
00:40:53,934 --> 00:40:55,934
To Momoko...

551
00:40:58,934 --> 00:41:01,934
I thought I'd propose as a surprise!

552
00:41:01,934 --> 00:41:03,934
A proposal!? Yes.

553
00:41:03,934 --> 00:41:06,934
It's just... it's just...→

554
00:41:06,934 --> 00:41:10,934
I lost my engagement ring...

555
00:41:10,934 --> 00:41:14,934
Hmm. Proposal...

556
00:41:18,934 --> 00:41:20,934
yes…. So were you looking for something?

557
00:41:20,934 --> 00:41:22,934
Hey….

558
00:41:24,934 --> 00:41:29,934
Listen to what you said earlier→

559
00:41:29,934 --> 00:41:33,934
I wanted to forget about the painful things from the past.

560
00:41:34,934 --> 00:41:36,934
I see...!

561
00:41:36,934 --> 00:41:38,934
Then then...!

562
00:41:38,934 --> 00:41:41,934
(Mio) Guaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa...!

563
00:41:41,934 --> 00:41:43,934
Ugh...! (All) Huh?

564
00:41:43,934 --> 00:41:45,934
(sigh)

565
00:41:48,934 --> 00:41:50,934
I can't take it.

566
00:41:50,934 --> 00:41:54,934
Eh, an engagement ring!? Eh, why is Mio-nee wearing it!?

567
00:41:54,934 --> 00:41:57,934
I think it has something to do with the incident...

568
00:41:57,934 --> 00:41:59,934
No, where... (Mio) Wait a minute, wait, wait...

569
00:41:59,934 --> 00:42:01,934
Hey bud. yes.

570
00:42:01,934 --> 00:42:04,934
I see. Are you going to marry Mio-nee?

571
00:42:04,934 --> 00:42:06,934
no…. Yes, yes, yes.

572
00:42:06,934 --> 00:42:09,934
I see. Congratulations!

573
00:42:09,934 --> 00:42:12,934
No, it's not. It's a false accusation!

574
00:42:12,934 --> 00:42:14,934
Hahahaha…! Ugh...!

575
00:42:14,934 --> 00:42:16,934
Sigh… I got it!

576
00:42:16,934 --> 00:42:18,934
Oh good. It's late...

577
00:42:18,934 --> 00:42:20,934
(Mio) Look, look, look…. Please return it.

578
00:42:20,934 --> 00:42:22,934
(Mio) Look... now...

579
00:42:22,934 --> 00:42:24,934
Huh? Now now now….

580
00:42:24,934 --> 00:42:26,934
Now!? (Mio) Now! Huh!

581
00:42:26,934 --> 00:42:46,934
♬〜

582
00:42:46,934 --> 00:42:49,934
ah…. Mecha old man!

583
00:42:49,934 --> 00:42:52,934
(Soichiro Midorikawa) Thank you for your hard work. What is it?

584
00:42:52,934 --> 00:42:55,934
Mecha old man, give me the money back.

585
00:42:55,934 --> 00:42:57,934
I'll get back to you, so just listen.

586
00:42:59,934 --> 00:43:03,934
Thank you for making me your seventh detective.

587
00:43:04,934 --> 00:43:07,934
What happened?

588
00:43:07,934 --> 00:43:09,934
Yeah.

589
00:43:09,934 --> 00:43:11,934
I decided to retire today.

590
00:43:11,934 --> 00:43:14,934
Old wounds hurt.

591
00:43:15,934 --> 00:43:19,934
(Midorikawa) I have decided to quit being the maintenance advisor for this truck.

592
00:43:20,934 --> 00:43:24,934
Everyone took good care of me.

593
00:43:25,934 --> 00:43:27,934
I'll leave the rest to you.

594
00:43:29,934 --> 00:43:32,934
(Midorikawa) Manager →

595
00:43:32,934 --> 00:43:35,934
Beautiful sister →

596
00:43:35,934 --> 00:43:38,934
peach→

597
00:43:38,934 --> 00:43:40,934
Kuro-san→

598
00:43:40,934 --> 00:43:42,934
Chef →

599
00:43:42,934 --> 00:43:44,934
bud.

600
00:43:46,934 --> 00:43:49,934
I asked for the first star.

601
00:43:49,934 --> 00:44:06,934
♬〜

602
00:44:06,934 --> 00:44:08,934
Did you hear that?

603
00:44:08,934 --> 00:44:11,934
Yeah...me too.

604
00:44:12,934 --> 00:44:14,934
Terrible noise...

605
00:44:20,934 --> 00:44:23,934
Mecha old man...→

606
00:44:23,934 --> 00:44:25,934
I lied.
